abstract: Pentagon reports killing of senior Islamic State leader Abu Bakr al-Turkmani by coalition forces during airstrike in northern Iraq; confirms that French jihadist David Drugeon, explosives expert and member of Al Qaeda offshoot Khorasan Group, died during airstrike in Syria in July.
lead_paragraph: A Pentagon spokesman, Peter Cook, described Abu Bakr al-Turkmani as an “administrative emir” of the Islamic State.

headline.main: Iraq: Airstrike Kills an ISIS Leader
